âœ… STEP 0: Prerequisites

AlmaLinux 8/9

Root or sudo user

Fresh system (LEMP removed already)

âœ… STEP 1: Update system
sudo dnf update -y
(sudo dnf install epel-release)
sudo dnf install nano

âœ… STEP 2: Install NGINX
sudo dnf install -y nginx
sudo systemctl enable nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx


Test:

curl http://localhost


You should see NGINX default page.

âœ… STEP 3: Install PHP (with WordPress requirements)
sudo dnf install -y \
php php-fpm php-mysqlnd php-cli php-common \
php-gd php-xml php-mbstring php-json php-opcache php-curl php-zip

ðŸ”´ CRITICAL: Fix PHP-FPM socket (most common failure)

Edit:

sudo vi /etc/php-fpm.d/www.conf


Set exactly:

user = nginx
group = nginx

listen = /run/php-fpm/www.sock
listen.owner = nginx
listen.group = nginx
listen.mode = 0660


Start PHP:

sudo systemctl enable php-fpm
sudo systemctl start php-fpm


Verify:

ls -l /run/php-fpm/www.sock


Owner must be nginx:nginx

âœ… STEP 4: Install MariaDB
sudo dnf install -y mariadb mariadb-server
sudo systemctl enable mariadb
sudo systemctl start mariadb


Secure it:

sudo mariadb-secure-installation


Choose:

Set root password â†’ Yes

Remove anonymous users â†’ Yes

Disallow remote root login â†’ Yes

Remove test DB â†’ Yes

Reload privileges â†’ Yes

âœ… STEP 5: Create WordPress database
sudo mariadb

CREATE DATABASE wordpress
  DEFAULT CHARACTER SET utf8mb4
  COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;

CREATE USER 'wuser'@'localhost'
IDENTIFIED BY 'wpass';

GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON wordpress.* TO 'wuser'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
EXIT;


Test:

mariadb -u wuser -p wordpress

âœ… STEP 6: Download WordPress
cd /var/www/html
sudo wget https://wordpress.org/latest.tar.gz
sudo tar -xzf latest.tar.gz
sudo rm -f latest.tar.gz


Permissions:

sudo chown -R nginx:nginx /var/www/html/wordpress
sudo find /var/www/html/wordpress -type d -exec chmod 755 {} \;
sudo find /var/www/html/wordpress -type f -exec chmod 644 {} \;

âœ… STEP 7: NGINX virtual host (WordPress)

Create config:

sudo vi /etc/nginx/conf.d/wordpress.conf


Paste:

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _;
    root /var/www/html/wordpress;
    index index.php index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$args;
    }

    location ~ \.php$ {
        try_files $uri =404;
        include fastcgi.conf;
        fastcgi_pass unix:/run/php-fpm/www.sock;
    }

    location ~ /\.(?!well-known).* {
        deny all;
    }
}


Test & reload:

sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx

âœ… STEP 8: WordPress config file
cd /var/www/html/wordpress
sudo cp wp-config-sample.php wp-config.php
sudo vi wp-config.php


Set:

define( 'DB_NAME', 'wordpress' );
define( 'DB_USER', 'wuser' );
define( 'DB_PASSWORD', 'wpass' );
define( 'DB_HOST', 'localhost' );


Fix permissions:

sudo chown nginx:nginx wp-config.php
sudo chmod 640 wp-config.php

âœ… STEP 9: SELinux (MANDATORY on AlmaLinux)
sudo setsebool -P httpd_can_network_connect_db 1
sudo chcon -R -t httpd_sys_content_t /var/www/html/wordpress

âœ… STEP 10: Restart everything
sudo systemctl restart mariadb php-fpm
sudo systemctl reload nginx

âœ… STEP 11: Finish WordPress install

Open browser:

http://SERVER_IP/


You should see WordPress installation page ðŸŽ‰

ðŸ§  MACHINE-TEST CHECKLIST (MEMORIZE THIS)

NGINX running

PHP executes (phpinfo())

PHP-FPM socket owned by nginx

php-mysqlnd installed

MariaDB running

DB + user exists

wp-config.php correct

SELinux boolean enabled

If you remember these â†’ you will pass.
